Hi Bjarne Andersen,

&gt; Since upgrading from 0.7.1 to 0.10.0 I have problems when running 
&gt; Heritrix without the GUI
&gt; 
&gt; I used to simply start the crawler with
&gt; 
&gt; $HERITRIX_HOME/bin/heritrix -n order.xml
&gt; 
&gt; the paths in order.xml where all relative to the placement of the order.xml
&gt; 
&gt; when I do the same now the paths specified in order.xml are calculated 
&gt; relatively to the root of my filesystem which means that the crawler 
&gt; tries to save files in:
&gt; /arcs
&gt; /logs
&gt; /state
&gt; /checkpoint
&gt; 
&gt; If I specify absolut paths in the order.xml everything runs fine !
&gt; 
&gt; And now for the question - do I miss any setting / configuration to 
&gt; obtain the old style path-calculating - or is this a new practice ?

This sounds like a bug to me. I will take a look it and will make an bug issue at sourceforge.
